The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Sanath, Ajantha get the Cup axe 
                                                                                                                       7                                      Sanath, Ajantha get the Cup axe 
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: Veteran Sri Lanka cricketer Sanath Jayasuriya and mystery spinner Ajantha Mendis were Wednesday dropped from the 15-member squad for the Asia Cup that begins in the island nation on June 15.         
	Regular skipper Kumar Sangakkara and off-spinner Muttiah Muralitharan, who were rested for the tri-nation series in Zimbabwe, returned to the squad for the tournament which also features India, Pakistan and Bangladesh.         
	Former skipper Mahela Jayawardene and pacer Lasith Malinga, too, were back in the side after being rested.         
	Tillekaratne Dilshan, who captained Sri Lanka to the series win in Zimbabwe, and opener Upul Tharanga were retained.         
	However, middle-order batsman Chamara Silva and fast bowler Dilhara Fernando, who were in the side for the tri-series in Zimbabwe, were overlooked.         
	The Squad         
	Kumar Sangakkara (C), Muttiah Muralidharan (VC), Tillekaratne Dilshan, Upul Tharanga, Mahela Jayawardene, Lasith Malinga, Angelo Mathews, Thilan Samaraweera, Fervez Mahroof, Chamara Kapugedera, Nuwan Kulasekera, Chanaka Welagedara, Suraj Randiv, Rangana Herath, Thilina Kandamby.                                                                                                                     
